<div type="edition" xml:lang="bya-Latn"><!-- maybe use more refined language classification to be able to process differences between Toba and other Batak languages -->
    <div type="textpart" n="1">
    <head xml:lang="eng">Introduction: list of instances when to perform the ritual</head>
    <p>
    <pb n="A1"/>
    <!-- https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1k5glbG6ZVixzG0ttBMbrOy0HHSaPad14 -->
    <lb n="A1-1"/><g type="B1"/> poda ni pamusatana· ni paro·bu<lb
    n="A1-2" break="no"/><space quantity="corresp-B1-lb1"/><!-- how to encode such cases is to be discussed with Axelle -->kitana· beya di karo·ja sita<lb
    n="A1-3" break="no"/>-sita, beya kita dipadatu kalaka· di kasukutano· na bolano·, beya <unclear>k</unclear>i<lb
    n="A1-4" break="no"/>⌉ta dipadatu kalaka· manusaku· kuta
      <choice><orig>rib</orig><reg>rimb</reg></choice>aru, 
    <!-- other encoding options
      2. ri<choice><orig>b</orig><reg>mb</reg></choice>aru,
      3. <choice><orig>ri</orig><reg>rami·</reg></choice>baru,
      4. ri<supplied reason="subaudible">m</supplied>baru, -->
      beya kita maro·dom<unclear>u</unclear> <unclear>ba</unclear><lb
      n="A1-5" break="no"/>ho, beya kita maṅase home di juma di kasukutano·, beya kita ma<unclear>tu</unclear>
    <lb n="A1-6"/>tu haheka·hanaka·tubu, beya paro·sakana· ni na mate matuva, beya di <supplied reason="lost">b</supplied>-
    <lb n="A1-7"/>-isara na godaṁ.
    </p>
</div>
    <div type="textpart" n="2">
    <head  xml:lang="eng">Invocations and enumeration of the <hi rend="italic">datu</hi> through which the instructions have been handed down</head>
    <p>Hasa daIda ma karorobo ni <choice><orig>karo·bota</orig><reg>karo·bonta</reg></choice> Inano· hasa da<unclear>b</unclear>-
    <lb n="8"/>-oto monaṁ kita di kasukutano·ni, daboto kita dapotana·<supplied reason="lost">da</supplied>
    <lb n="9"/>boto kita talu di kata ni paro·bukitana·ta Inano·,<choice><orig>nina</orig><reg>ninta</reg></choice>guru<choice><orig>guruta</orig><reg></reg></choice>
    <lb n="10"/> guru hagana·ni haji ho I, hasa kupodakano· ma di ko hale guru tumura<unclear>nu·</unclear>
    <lb n="11"/>ni haji, hasa ro ma di ko guru so dupaṅano·ni haji datuparo·ta<unclear>n</unclear>
    <lb n="12"/>·daṁ bolano·tu banuva ni kalaka· sumarikano· homas· sigumar<unclear>o</unclear>
    <lb n="13"/>·siṁ, hasa ro ma di ko hale <choice><orig>hopu</orig><reg>hompu</reg></choice> ni maṅalebana·namora karo di <choice><sic>tana</sic><corr>tano</corr></choice> sira
    <lb n="14"/>hati·, hasa ro ma di ko datu paṁguhala·ni haji ho. Iya, gohara· maram-
    <lb n="15"/>-o·puni <choice><orig>hopu</orig><reg>hompu</reg></choice> tuvana· binaru·kata ni haji datu paro·tan·daṁ bolan-
    <lb n="16"/>-o· ganapu· desa liyata· paro·tibi sumarikano· homasa· siguma
    <lb n="17"/>ro· siṁ parotaṅan· na palohano· paro·jari-jari sirurasu·dibake
    <lb n="18"/>na· sikumisaki· di lobuhana· na godaṁ pana·samato· so taridad-
    <lb n="19"/>-o hakutiyana·tano palipi namora sinaga <choice><orig>hopu</orig><reg>hompu</reg></choice> ratasu·na sonuṁ talu
    <lb n="20"/>di bisara na godaṁ maṅasakano·paṅulubalaṁ duva raja hojami·na bolan-
    <lb n="21"/>-o· maṅasakano· panuruni balagori na bolano· maṅasakano· pabukutana·
    <lb n="22"/>daku· si haṁgasa na simanako·toki na sotarulaka· baho datu na so tara·
    <lb n="23"/>su batu·boru si baso bolano· hasa kupodakano· ma diko hale lahe da
    <lb n="24"/>tu paro·kasa· kata ni haji ho I; gohara· kadatuhano· ma Inano·
    </p>
